Vice President Joe Biden and Dr. Jill Biden released a statement on the passing of John Glenn, expressing their admiration for his heroism and love for his country and family. They described Glenn and his wife Annie as a true partnership that embodied humility and a sense of duty. The Bidens considered themselves blessed to have known the Glenns for many years and offered their condolences to Annie, their children, and the entire Glenn family. They believed that future generations of Americans can learn from Glenn's life and find inspiration in his example of exploration, service, and love for his country. The statement concluded with the sentiment, "Godspeed, friend."